{'hadithnumber': 101, 'text': '"Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) chose a signet ring of gold, and he used to wear it on his right hand. The people therefore chose signet rings of gold, so he threw it away (Allah bless him and give him peace) and said: \'I shall never wear it!\' The people therefore threw their signet rings away.”'}
{'hadithnumber': 102, 'text': '“Ihe pommel of the sword of Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) was made of silver.”'}
{'hadithnumber': 103, 'text': '“The pommel of the sword of Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) was made of silver."'}
{'hadithnumber': 104, 'text': '"Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) entered Mecca on the Day of Victory with gold and silver on his sword. An inquirer said: \'I asked him about the silver\', and he said: ‘The pommel of the sword was silver\'.”'}
{'hadithnumber': 105, 'text': '"I made my sword in the shape of the sword of Samura ibn Jundub." Samura also claimed that he made his sword in the shape of the sword of Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace), for he was a Hanafi.'}
{'hadithnumber': 106, 'text': '"The Prophet (Allah bless him and give him peace) wore two coats of mail on the Day of \\nUhud, so he tried to climb the boulder but was not able. He therefore made Talha sit\\nbeneath him, and the Prophet (Allah bless him and give him peace), climbed up until he stood upright on the rock." He said: "I heard the Prophet say (Allah bless him and give\\nhim peace): \'Talha performed a deed worthy of reward\'!”'}
{'hadithnumber': 107, 'text': '"Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) wore on the Day of Uhud two coats of mail between which he rendered support.”'}
{'hadithnumber': 108, 'text': '"The Prophet (Allah bless him and give him peace) entered Mecca wearing a helmet. He was told: \'This Ibn Khatal  is clinging to the curtains of the Ka\'ba so he said: \'Kill him!\'"'}
{'hadithnumber': 109, 'text': "“Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) entered Mecca in the Year of Victory with the helmet on his head. When he took it off, a man came to him and told him: ‘Ibn Khatal  is clinging to the curtains of the Ka'ba,’ so he said: ‘Kill him!’ Ibn Shihab said: ‘It has also reached me that Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) was not in the state of ritual consecration on that day.’”"}
{'hadithnumber': 110, 'text': '“The Prophet (Allah bless him and give him peace) entered Mecca on the Day of Victory wearing a black turban.”'}
{'hadithnumber': 111, 'text': '"I saw a black turban on the head of Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace).”'}
{'hadithnumber': 112, 'text': '"The Prophet (Allah bless him and give him peace) addressed the people while wearing a black turban.”'}
{'hadithnumber': 113, 'text': '"When the Prophet (Allah bless him and give him peace) donned a turban, he let his turban hang down between his shoulders.”'}
{'hadithnumber': 114, 'text': '“The Prophet (Allah bless him and give him peace) addressed the people while wearing a turban that was dasma’ .'}
{'hadithnumber': 115, 'text': "“'A'isha (may Allah be well pleased with her) brought out to us a tangled garment and a coarse loincloth, then she said: ‘The spirit of Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) was taken in these two'.”"}
{'hadithnumber': 116, 'text': '"I heard my maternal aunt relate, on the authority of her paternal uncle; \'While I was walking in Medina, someone behind me said: ‘Raise your loincloth, for that is more pious and conducive to longer wear.’ Lo and behold, he was Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace)\', so I said: ‘O Messenger of Allah, it is simply a black garment with white stripes!’ He said: ‘Do you not have an example in me?’ so I looked and noticed that his loincloth was to half his shins\'.”'}
{'hadithnumber': 117, 'text': '"\'Uthman ibn \'Affan used to wear a loincloth reaching the middle parts of his shins, and he said: \'In this manner was the loincloth of my Companion\', meaning the Prophet (Allah bless him and give him peace).”'}
{'hadithnumber': 118, 'text': '"Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) took hold of the calf of my legs or his leg, and he said: \'This is the position of the loincloth, and if you object, then somewhat lower down, but if you object, the loincloth has no right to the ankles\'.”'}
{'hadithnumber': 119, 'text': '"I have not seen anything more beautiful than Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace). The sun seemed to shine in his face. Nor have I seen anyone more rapid in his gait than Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace). The earth seemed to be folded up for him. We must strenuously exert ourselves, while he is not subject to any stress."'}
{'hadithnumber': 120, 'text': '“When "Ali described the Prophet (Allah bless him and give him peace), he said: ‘When he walked, he moved as if he were descending a declivity\'.”'}
{'hadithnumber': 121, 'text': '"When the Prophet (Allah bless him and give him peace) walked, he inclined forward as if he were descending a declivity.”'}
{'hadithnumber': 122, 'text': '“Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) would often wear the head veil, as if his robe was the robe of an oil dealer.”'}
{'hadithnumber': 123, 'text': 'Qaila bint Makhrama said that she saw Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) in the mosque squatting on his heels. She said: "When I saw Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) displaying humility in the mosque, I trembled with fright."'}
{'hadithnumber': 124, 'text': 'His paternal uncle said that he saw the Prophet (Allah bless him and give him peace) lying on his back in the mosque, placing one of his legs over the other.'}
{'hadithnumber': 125, 'text': '“When Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) sat in the mosque, he pressed his legs against his stomach with his hands.”'}
{'hadithnumber': 126, 'text': '"I saw Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) leaning on a cushion on his left side.”'}
{'hadithnumber': 127, 'text': "“Allah’s Messenger said (Allah bless him and give him peace): ‘Should I tell you about the greatest of the major sins?’ They said: ‘Yes indeed, O Messenger of Allah!’ He said: ‘Associating partners with Allah, and recalcitrance against parents.’ Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) sat down, and he was leaning on a support. He added: '...and false testimony’ or: ‘false speech.’ Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) went on speaking until we said: ‘If only he would keep silent!”"}
{'hadithnumber': 128, 'text': '"Allah’s Messenger said (Allah bless him and give him peace):‘As for me, I do not eat while leaning on a support!’”'}
{'hadithnumber': 129, 'text': '"Allah’s Messenger said (Allah bless him and give him peace): \'I do not eat while leaning on a support! I do not eat while leaning on a support\'!”'}
{'hadithnumber': 130, 'text': '"I saw Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) leaning on a cushion.”'}
{'hadithnumber': 131, 'text': '“The Prophet (Allah bless him and give him peace) was feeling ill, so he came out leaning on Usama ibn Zaid wearing an outer garment of coarse cotton fabric, which he had thrown on loosely, after which he led them in the ritual prayer.”'}
{'hadithnumber': 132, 'text': '"I went in to see Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) during his illness in which he died, and on his head there was a yellow band. I greeted him with the salutation of peace, so he said: \'O Fadl!”\'I said: \'Doubly at your service, O Messenger of Allah!\' He said: \'Wrap my head firmly with this band!\' I acted accordingly, then he sat and placed the palm of his hand on my shoulder. Then he stood up and entered the mosque.” (This tradition is part of a longer story.)'}
{'hadithnumber': 133, 'text': '"The Prophet (Allah bless him and give him peace) used to lick his fingers three times.”'}
{'hadithnumber': 134, 'text': '“When the Prophet (Allah bless him and give him peace) ate a meal, he used to lick his three fingers .”'}
{'hadithnumber': 135, 'text': "“The Prophet said (Allah bless him and give him peace): 'As for me, I do not eat while leaning on a support'!”"}
{'hadithnumber': 136, 'text': '"Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) used to eat with his three fingers and afterwards he would lick them.”'}
{'hadithnumber': 137, 'text': '"Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) was brought some dried dates, and I saw him eat while he was hunched over from hunger.”'}
{'hadithnumber': 138, 'text': '"The family of Muhammad (Allah bless him and give him peace) did not satisfy their appetite with barley-bread for before even two consecutive days until Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) was taken from this world.”'}
{'hadithnumber': 139, 'text': '"There was never more than a bare sufficiency of barley- bread for the people of the household of Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace).”'}
{'hadithnumber': 140, 'text': '"Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) used to spend night after night starving. He and his family would not have any supper to eat, and most of their bread was barley-bread.”'}
{'hadithnumber': 141, 'text': '“Did Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) eat the finest flour, meaning white bread?” Sahl said: “Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) did not see the finest flour until he met Allah (Almighty and Glorious is He).” Then he was asked: “Did you have sieves in the time of Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace)?” He said: “We did not have sieves.” He was asked: “How did you treat barley?” He said: “We used to blow on it, so whatever flew would fly off it, and then we would knead it.”'}
{'hadithnumber': 142, 'text': '“Allah’s Prophet (Allah bless him and give him peace) did not eat food on a table, nor in a bowl, and no bread rolled thin and flat was baked for him. I asked Qatada: ‘So on\\nwhat were they used to eating?’ He said: ‘On these pieces of skin .”'}
{'hadithnumber': 143, 'text': '"I went in to see \'A\'isha, so she ordered a meal for me, and she said: “I do not eat my fill from a meal, for I feel like weeping, if I have not wept.” I said: “Why?” She said:\\n“I remember the state in which Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) departed from this world. By Allah, he did not eat his fill of bread and meat twice in one day!”'}
{'hadithnumber': 144, 'text': '"Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) did not eat his fill of barley-bread for two days in a row until he died.”'}
{'hadithnumber': 145, 'text': '“Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) did not eat food on a table, and he did not eat bread rolled thin and flat, until he died.”'}
{'hadithnumber': 146, 'text': "“Allah’s Messenger said (Allah bless him and give him peace): ‘What an excellent condiment vinegar is'!”"}
{'hadithnumber': 147, 'text': '“Do you not have what you want in the way of food and drink? I have seen your Prophet (Allah bless him and give him peace), and the poor-quality dates  that he finds are what fills his stomach."'}
{'hadithnumber': 148, 'text': "Allah’s Messenger said (Allah bless him and give him peace): 'What an excellent condiment vinegar is!’”"}
{'hadithnumber': 149, 'text': '"We were in the presence of Abu Musa al- Ash\'ari when he was brought some chicken meat. A man among the people thereupon turned away, so he asked him: \'What is the matter?\' He replied: \'I saw it eating something putrid, so I swore that I would not eat it.\' He  said: \'Draw near, for I have seen Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and\\ngive him peace) eating the meat of chickens\'!”'}
{'hadithnumber': 150, 'text': '"I ate together with Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) the meat of a bustard.”'}
